---
/**
 * Operator control: anatomy of a useful approval.
 *
 * A schematic of the six load-bearing pieces an operator needs in order
 * to say yes, no, or narrower. This diagram is principle-level; it is not
 * a UI mock and does not depict any specific product surface.
 *
 * Inline SVG with accessible <title> and <desc>, so text content is
 * indexable by search engines and readable by assistive tech.
 *
 * Used in: content/blog/operator-control-for-agentic-systems.mdx
 */
---

<figure class="diagram diagram--approval-anatomy">
  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1320 560" role="img" aria-labelledby="ocApprTitle ocApprDesc" font-family="system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif" font-size="15">
    <title id="ocApprTitle">What a useful approval communicates</title>
    <desc id="ocApprDesc">A schematic approval card divided into six labeled regions, with annotations pulled out to either side. The six regions are Action (what the agent intends to do, in one line), Why (the reasoning that produced the action), What will change (the concrete diff or writes the action causes), Risk (reversibility, blast radius, and scope of effect), Evidence (what the operator can read to decide), and Outcomes (Approve, Deny, or Narrow, with what happens after each). The diagram represents the principle of a useful approval, not any specific product surface.</desc>
    <defs>
      <marker id="arApr" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#64748b"/></marker>
      <style>.lane{fill:#f8fafc;stroke:#e2e8f0;stroke-width:1}.head{font-weight:700;fill:#0f172a;font-size:18px}.lbl{fill:#0f172a;font-weight:600}.sub{fill:#334155;font-size:14px}.note{fill:#475569;font-size:14px;font-style:italic}.dTitle{font-size:32px;font-weight:800;fill:#0f172a}.dSubtitle{font-size:16px;fill:#475569}.connDash{stroke:#94a3b8;stroke-width:1.5;fill:none;stroke-dasharray:4 3}.legendText{fill:#334155;font-size:14px}.legendTitle{font-size:13px;font-weight:700;fill:#334155;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase}.cardOuter{fill:#fffafa;stroke:#b91c1c;stroke-width:2.5}.cardHead{fill:#fee2e2;stroke:none}.cardHeadTitle{fill:#7f1d1d;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.rowLine{stroke:#fecaca;stroke-width:1;fill:none}.regionNum{fill:#b91c1c;font-size:13px;font-weight:700}.actionMono{fill:#1e293b;font-family:ui-monospace,SFMono-Regular,Menlo,Consolas,monospace;font-size:14px;font-weight:700}.changeMono{fill:#3f6212;font-family:ui-monospace,SFMono-Regular,Menlo,Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px}.evidenceMono{fill:#6d28d9;font-family:ui-monospace,SFMono-Regular,Menlo,Consolas,monospace;font-size:13px}.rowLabel{fill:#475569;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase}.btnApprove{fill:#dcfce7;stroke:#15803d;stroke-width:1.5}.btnDeny{fill:#fee2e2;stroke:#b91c1c;stroke-width:1.5}.btnNarrow{fill:#fef3c7;stroke:#b45309;stroke-width:1.5}.btnApproveText{fill:#15803d;font-weight:700;font-size:14px}.btnDenyText{fill:#b91c1c;font-weight:700;font-size:14px}.btnNarrowText{fill:#b45309;font-weight:700;font-size:14px}.riskPill{fill:#fef2f2;stroke:#b91c1c;stroke-width:1.25}.riskPillText{fill:#b91c1c;font-size:13px;font-weight:700}.annoBox{fill:#f8fafc;stroke:#cbd5e1;stroke-width:1}.annoTitle{fill:#0f172a;font-size:14px;font-weight:700}.annoText{fill:#334155;font-size:12.5px}</style>
    </defs>

    <!-- Header -->
    <text x="660" y="28" text-anchor="middle" class="dTitle">Anatomy of a Useful Approval</text>
    <text x="660" y="48" text-anchor="middle" class="dSubtitle">Six load-bearing pieces an operator needs in order to say yes, no, or narrower (not a UI mock, the principle)</text>

    <!-- Background lane -->
    <rect class="lane" x="20" y="74" width="1280" height="430" rx="8"/>

    <!-- CARD (center) -->
    <rect class="cardOuter" x="500" y="100" width="320" height="380" rx="10"/>
    <!-- Header bar -->
    <rect class="cardHead" x="500" y="100" width="320" height="36" rx="10"/>
    <rect class="cardHead" x="500" y="120" width="320" height="16"/>
    <text x="514" y="123" class="cardHeadTitle">approval requested</text>
    <text x="804" y="123" text-anchor="end" class="cardHeadTitle" fill="#7f1d1d">agent-3 · 14:07</text>

    <!-- Row 1: Action -->
    <text x="514" y="156" class="rowLabel">1 · Action</text>
    <text x="514" y="178" class="actionMono">POST /api/orgs/:id/seed-fund</text>
    <text x="514" y="194" class="sub">create a funding row with status <tspan class="actionMono" font-size="11">pending</tspan></text>
    <line class="rowLine" x1="510" y1="206" x2="810" y2="206"/>

    <!-- Row 2: Why -->
    <text x="514" y="222" class="rowLabel">2 · Why</text>
    <text x="514" y="240" class="sub">Spec step 4 says "seed the fund row before the wire job runs."</text>
    <text x="514" y="256" class="sub">Wire job is queued for 14:30. No row exists yet.</text>
    <line class="rowLine" x1="510" y1="266" x2="810" y2="266"/>

    <!-- Row 3: What will change -->
    <text x="514" y="282" class="rowLabel">3 · What will change</text>
    <text x="514" y="300" class="changeMono">+ db.funds  ·  1 row inserted</text>
    <text x="514" y="316" class="changeMono">+ audit_log ·  1 row appended</text>
    <text x="514" y="330" class="sub">no email, no external call, scope: this org only</text>
    <line class="rowLine" x1="510" y1="340" x2="810" y2="340"/>

    <!-- Row 4: Risk -->
    <text x="514" y="356" class="rowLabel">4 · Risk</text>
    <g>
      <rect class="riskPill" x="514" y="362" width="96" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="562" y="378" text-anchor="middle" class="riskPillText">REVERSIBLE</text>
      <rect class="riskPill" x="618" y="362" width="116" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="676" y="378" text-anchor="middle" class="riskPillText">SINGLE TENANT</text>
      <rect class="riskPill" x="742" y="362" width="78" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="781" y="378" text-anchor="middle" class="riskPillText">NO EGRESS</text>
    </g>
    <line class="rowLine" x1="510" y1="396" x2="810" y2="396"/>

    <!-- Row 5: Evidence -->
    <text x="514" y="412" class="rowLabel">5 · Evidence</text>
    <text x="514" y="430" class="evidenceMono">spec.md#L42 · last 3 tool calls · diff preview</text>
    <line class="rowLine" x1="510" y1="442" x2="810" y2="442"/>

    <!-- Row 6: Outcomes -->
    <text x="514" y="458" class="rowLabel">6 · Outcomes</text>
    <g>
      <rect class="btnApprove" x="514" y="463" width="84" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="556" y="479" text-anchor="middle" class="btnApproveText">approve</text>
      <rect class="btnDeny" x="606" y="463" width="68" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="640" y="479" text-anchor="middle" class="btnDenyText">deny</text>
      <rect class="btnNarrow" x="682" y="463" width="124" height="22" rx="11"/>
      <text x="744" y="479" text-anchor="middle" class="btnNarrowText">narrow + retry</text>
    </g>

    <!-- LEFT-SIDE ANNOTATIONS (for rows 1, 3, 5) -->
    <!-- Annotation 1: Action -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="40" y="148" width="380" height="62" rx="6"/>
    <text x="56" y="166" class="annoTitle">1 · The action, named, in one line</text>
    <text x="56" y="184" class="annoText">What the agent intends to do, verb-first, parameters legible.</text>
    <text x="56" y="200" class="annoText">Not "do the thing." Not "complete the workflow." The actual call.</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M420 179 L500 179" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- Annotation 3: What will change -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="40" y="276" width="380" height="76" rx="6"/>
    <text x="56" y="294" class="annoTitle">3 · The concrete delta</text>
    <text x="56" y="312" class="annoText">Which rows, which files, which calls go out. Anything that</text>
    <text x="56" y="328" class="annoText">touches external systems is named explicitly here.</text>
    <text x="56" y="344" class="annoText" font-style="italic">"a row is inserted" beats "a write happens."</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M420 314 L500 314" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- Annotation 5: Evidence -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="40" y="404" width="380" height="62" rx="6"/>
    <text x="56" y="422" class="annoTitle">5 · The evidence the operator can read</text>
    <text x="56" y="440" class="annoText">Pointers, not summaries: the spec line, the prior tool calls,</text>
    <text x="56" y="456" class="annoText">the diff preview. Operator decides what counts as enough.</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M420 435 L500 435" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- RIGHT-SIDE ANNOTATIONS (for rows 2, 4, 6) -->
    <!-- Annotation 2: Why -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="900" y="212" width="380" height="62" rx="6"/>
    <text x="916" y="230" class="annoTitle">2 · The reasoning that led here</text>
    <text x="916" y="248" class="annoText">Why this action, now. Tied to the spec, ticket, or instruction</text>
    <text x="916" y="264" class="annoText">the agent is working from. Reviewable independent of the action.</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M820 240 L900 240" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- Annotation 4: Risk -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="900" y="346" width="380" height="62" rx="6"/>
    <text x="916" y="364" class="annoTitle">4 · The risk profile</text>
    <text x="916" y="382" class="annoText">Reversible? Blast radius? External-facing? These shape</text>
    <text x="916" y="398" class="annoText">the operator's bar; same action can need different scrutiny.</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M820 374 L900 374" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- Annotation 6: Outcomes -->
    <rect class="annoBox" x="900" y="445" width="380" height="48" rx="6"/>
    <text x="916" y="463" class="annoTitle">6 · Three outcomes, not two</text>
    <text x="916" y="481" class="annoText">"Narrow" matters: scope this down, keep the agent moving.</text>
    <path class="connDash" d="M820 471 L900 471" marker-end="url(#arApr)"/>

    <!-- Caveat strip -->
    <text x="660" y="528" text-anchor="middle" class="note">Schematic, not a product surface. The shape is the point: every row carries weight an operator needs to make a real call.</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    Figure 3. What a useful approval communicates. Action, why, what will change, risk, evidence, and three outcomes. Not the surface, not the chrome, but the load-bearing pieces an operator needs in order to say yes, no, or narrower. A vague popup is interruption. A schema like this is responsibility made legible.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
